Ahmadabad Culture and Technology Complex () is a cultural center and village in Esmailabad Rural District of Bostan District in Baharestan County, Tehran province, Iran.
Demographics
Population
At the time of the 2006 National Census, the village's population was 35 in 10 households, when it was in Robat Karim County. The population at the 2011 census was below the reporting threshold, by which time the district had been separated from the county in the establishment of Baharestan County. The 2016 census measured the population of the village as zero. It was the only village in its rural district.
